    "rationale": "This example shows the oxidation of a simple, acyclic primary alcohol (1-nonanol) to the corresponding aldehyde (nonanal). This is a classic textbook transformation for the Pfitzner-Moffatt oxidation. The reagents shown are dimethyl sulfoxide (DMSO), dicyclohexylcarbodiimide (DCC), and pyridinium hydrochloride as the mild acid catalyst, which are the defining components of this reaction. The long alkyl chain helps avoid volatility and ensures the core transformation is the focus, while remaining simple and acyclic.",
